19
00:01:40,930 --> 00:01:43,600
[Episode 18]

20
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,490
Stop right there.

21
00:01:47,490 --> 00:01:49,600
What are you doing here?

22
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:51,340
Nothing.

23
00:01:51,340 --> 00:01:53,699
I just came to check on you.

24
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:57,239
I'm worried that you might get rejected and have no shoulder to cry on.

25
00:01:57,239 --> 00:01:58,699
Get out of here. I don't need a third wheel here.

26
00:01:59,930 --> 00:02:02,739
Ungrateful rascal. I'm leaving.

27
00:02:04,290 --> 00:02:05,160
Wait.

28
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:07,770
- Help me to...
- What do you mean by "there are only three months left"?

29
00:02:09,140 --> 00:02:11,200
His brain function index and EMG parameters have decreased.

30
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:13,880
know all these. Isn't this normal? It happened to him before

31
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:16,090
The stats aren't improving.

32
00:02:16,090 --> 00:02:17,819
It has started to decline day by day?

33
00:02:17,819 --> 00:02:20,879
Once it drops to zero... It... It would...

34
00:02:20,879 --> 00:02:24,350
It would... It would mean brain death?

35
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:05,800
I'll give you another chance.

36
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:08,740
If all else fails, I'll make a move.

37
00:05:43,780 --> 00:05:45,400
Do you like it?

38
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:47,970
Yes.

39
00:05:47,970 --> 00:05:50,470
Is this the surprise you prepared for me?

40
00:05:51,180 --> 00:05:55,889
Other than this, do you want to tell me anything else?

41
00:05:55,889 --> 00:05:57,570
I like you.

42
00:05:58,790 --> 00:06:00,740
I know that.

43
00:06:02,910 --> 00:06:06,760
But you don't know I've had a crush on you

44
00:06:07,420 --> 00:06:09,540
for a very long time now.

45
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:23,680
Hand over the money.

46
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:41,700
What are you doing? Don't you know this is school violence?

47
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:45,440
I've called the security office. It'll only take them a few minutes to reach here.

48
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:48,179
Two minutes are enough for me to beat you two to a pulp.

49
00:06:48,180 --> 00:06:49,659
They're over here!

50
00:06:49,660 --> 00:06:51,200
Run.

51
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:57,640
July 1st, 2014, was the first time we met.

52
00:07:06,890 --> 00:07:09,740
I can't control myself.

53
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:12,979
Are you okay?

54
00:07:12,979 --> 00:07:14,419
Run now.

55
00:07:14,419 --> 00:07:19,680
I can hear everyone's thoughts and control everyone's movement.

56
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:22,010
But I couldn't hear your thoughts.

57
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:25,990
You're an exception and a surprise too.

58
00:07:26,890 --> 00:07:31,800
You're just like a shield that makes me feel calm.

59
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:40,109
♫  I can see meteors through your eyes  ♫

60
00:07:40,109 --> 00:07:42,440
What are you doing? Don't run!

61
00:07:42,440 --> 00:07:44,180
Let's get out of here.

62
00:07:44,180 --> 00:07:46,659
♫  The love I've kept hidden in my youth  ♫

63
00:07:46,660 --> 00:07:48,200
Don't run!

64
00:07:49,210 --> 00:07:50,690
Stop right there!

65
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:55,079
Why don't I remember any of these?

66
00:07:55,079 --> 00:07:57,990
You'll know if you follow me.

67
00:08:01,230 --> 00:08:04,459
Come! Quick! Hurry up.

68
00:08:10,910 --> 00:08:12,890
I can't run anymore.

69
00:08:15,660 --> 00:08:17,880
I'm exhausted.

70
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:24,420
Thank you for helping me.

71
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:27,519
It's not a big deal. I didn't help at all.

72
00:08:28,660 --> 00:08:31,709
Hello. My name is Song Qingchun.

73
00:08:33,180 --> 00:08:35,919
Hello. I'm Su Zhinian.

74
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:42,340
Your nose... I'll get you a tissue.

75
00:08:42,340 --> 00:08:43,880
Wait. I'm fine.

76
00:08:43,880 --> 00:08:47,820
Does it hurt? Here.

77
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:54,099
- My treat.
- Thanks.

78
00:08:54,099 --> 00:08:57,229
Coca-cola is sweet, cold, and refreshing.

79
00:08:57,229 --> 00:08:59,920
Why do you like that tasteless soda drink?

80
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:01,780
Oh, I get it.

81
00:09:01,780 --> 00:09:03,199
It rhymes with your last name.

82
00:09:03,199 --> 00:09:06,520
That's why you like soda drinks.

83
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:09,210
That was such a lousy joke.

84
00:09:13,900 --> 00:09:16,100
Do you have superpowers?

85
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:19,520
Those guys couldn't control themselves just now. They couldn't even hit us.

86
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:24,430
So are you Superman or Iron Man?

87
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:28,199
- Aren't you scared of me?
- Why should I?

88
00:09:28,199 --> 00:09:30,429
If it weren't for you, they would've beaten me to a pulp.

89
00:09:30,429 --> 00:09:32,099
But don't worry.

90
00:09:32,099 --> 00:09:35,560
I'll help you keep this a secret so no one would capture and experiment on you.

91
00:09:35,560 --> 00:09:38,900
So can I ask you a favor?

92
00:09:40,020 --> 00:09:42,880
Can I go and see you more often in the future?

93
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:46,319
I mean, you have great grades.

94
00:09:46,319 --> 00:09:48,640
You can tutor me.

95
00:09:50,540 --> 00:09:52,320
Sure.

96
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:53,879
Don't forget, then.

97
00:09:53,879 --> 00:09:55,929
My name is Song Qingchun.

98
00:09:55,929 --> 00:09:57,780
Don't worry.

99
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:00,320
I've already memorized it.

100
00:10:01,090 --> 00:10:02,520
Cheers.

101
00:10:14,930 --> 00:10:16,730
- Sorry.
- What?

102
00:10:16,730 --> 00:10:19,480
I can't let you remember what happened today.

103
00:10:33,830 --> 00:10:35,570
I'll come back for you.

104
00:10:41,340 --> 00:10:45,220
[July 1st, 2014]

105
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:51,790
- So that's what happened.
- Sorry about that.

106
00:10:51,790 --> 00:10:55,550
Everything that happened in the Song family afterward, I'm sure you already know.

107
00:10:55,550 --> 00:11:00,359
While I was overseas, there was nothing to say other than working and studying.

108
00:11:00,359 --> 00:11:04,449
Until I watched your interview, I knew you were still single.

109
00:11:04,449 --> 00:11:09,930
So I set Geiger Capital up in Jiangli due to my personal interest.

110
00:11:10,710 --> 00:11:14,869
So when Huateng was in a crisis, you showed up all of a sudden

111
00:11:14,869 --> 00:11:19,349
to clean up this mess together with me even when I treated you like an enemy.

112
00:11:19,349 --> 00:11:21,990
Do you know how unprofessional it is for you to do this?

113
00:11:21,990 --> 00:11:26,289
If this gets out, no one will trust Geiger Capital's investments anymore.

114
00:11:26,289 --> 00:11:27,489
Not at all.

115
00:11:27,489 --> 00:11:31,639
Your transformation has solved the problem for me.

116
00:11:34,330 --> 00:11:37,990
After waiting for so many years, you must be tired.

117
00:11:37,990 --> 00:11:39,830
Better be late than never.

118
00:11:39,830 --> 00:11:45,489
Meeting you again and being with you day and night is all worth it.

119
00:11:45,489 --> 00:11:47,959
In the past, I only cared about my work.

120
00:11:47,959 --> 00:11:50,829
Now, I would always think

121
00:11:50,829 --> 00:11:54,159
about waiting for you every day before and after work.

122
00:11:55,380 --> 00:11:59,229
Over the weekends, I can accompany you to watch your favorite Korean series.

123
00:11:59,229 --> 00:12:03,059
But whenever you called "Oppa," I'd be jealous.

124
00:12:03,059 --> 00:12:05,830
I could only snatch the remote from you.

125
00:12:05,830 --> 00:12:09,139
Also, now I have someone to eat with me.

126
00:12:09,139 --> 00:12:14,559
For the first time, I became interested in the crowded supermarket and home cooking.

127
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:20,789
Your presence made my life more exciting

128
00:12:20,810 --> 00:12:23,090
and made me look forward to the future more.

129
00:12:23,930 --> 00:12:26,890
I like you, Song Qingchun.

130
00:12:30,810 --> 00:12:34,290
What did you say? Say that again.

131
00:12:35,930 --> 00:12:37,450
I like you.

132
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:43,110
I'm falling head over heels for you.

133
00:13:52,810 --> 00:13:54,710
What present are you going to give me?

134
00:13:54,710 --> 00:13:57,729
Why did you bring me to my old house? The bank has already seized this house.

135
00:13:57,729 --> 00:13:59,440
Come with me.

136
00:14:11,509 --> 00:14:13,029
Let's go.

137
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:22,960
[Seized by the First Intermediate People's Court
of Jiangli Municipality]

138
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:25,629
What are you doing? It's illegal.

139
00:14:26,610 --> 00:14:29,959
Back to its rightful owner. Take a look inside.

140
00:14:57,230 --> 00:14:59,970
I planned to reminisce.

141
00:14:59,970 --> 00:15:04,559
I didn't expect you to have destroyed the traces of my life here so thoroughly.

142
00:15:04,559 --> 00:15:06,330
Don't be mad.

143
00:15:07,090 --> 00:15:10,930
That's... That's because I've misunderstood you, then.

144
00:15:16,770 --> 00:15:18,970
What is this doing here?

145
00:15:23,060 --> 00:15:26,679
You already looked like a veteran cadre at 19 years old.

146
00:15:27,810 --> 00:15:31,169
This was when the school took pictures of excellent graduates.

147
00:15:31,169 --> 00:15:34,079
This photo is the only copy. They didn't give it to me.

148
00:15:34,760 --> 00:15:36,330
I'll confiscate this.

149
00:15:43,230 --> 00:15:46,330
"Happy birthday to Song Qingchun."

150
00:15:47,570 --> 00:15:49,059
Was this for me?

151
00:15:49,060 --> 00:15:50,470
I didn't know about this.

152
00:15:50,470 --> 00:15:52,710
Is it Jay Chou or Jolin Tsai?

153
00:16:26,060 --> 00:16:28,689
It's almost time. I have to clean up the place.

154
00:16:28,689 --> 00:16:30,960
You've been practicing the birthday song for a month.

155
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:34,069
I guess an excellent student is not good at everything.

156
00:16:34,069 --> 00:16:35,670
Thanks.

157
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:45,929
You promised to celebrate my birthday with me. I have to clean up the place.

158
00:16:45,929 --> 00:16:48,480
I'll never believe you again.

159
00:17:43,910 --> 00:17:47,360
- Happy birthday, Qing Chun.
- Thank you, Brother Yinan.

160
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:48,980
Here's the ticket to our school dance.

161
00:17:48,980 --> 00:17:51,889
There's a piano performance tomorrow. Don't be late.

162
00:17:51,889 --> 00:17:53,470
I won't.

163
00:17:53,470 --> 00:17:56,429
I like hearing you play the piano the most, so I won't be late.

164
00:17:56,429 --> 00:17:57,910
Don't worry.

165
00:18:05,470 --> 00:18:08,160
Why didn't you give it to me, then?

166
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:10,459
It's not that important.

167
00:18:10,459 --> 00:18:13,090
How do you know whether it's important to me?

168
00:18:13,090 --> 00:18:15,309
You didn't even tell me that you prepared the longevity noodles.

169
00:18:15,309 --> 00:18:18,430
I thought it was Brother Yinan who made it for me.

170
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:22,980
"Best Dunker's Cup"

171
00:18:23,850 --> 00:18:26,570
I remembered the trophy was...

172
00:19:02,060 --> 00:19:04,469
He just temporarily left the arena of the American Professional Basketball League.

173
00:19:04,469 --> 00:19:06,550
It's not that we'll never see him again.

174
00:19:09,330 --> 00:19:12,960
But my youth has come to an end.

175
00:19:12,960 --> 00:19:17,940
Also, I haven't gotten his signed jersey.

176
00:19:17,940 --> 00:19:22,870
Don't cry. It's only a jersey. I'll figure it out.

177
00:19:23,810 --> 00:19:25,599
- Really?
- Yes.

178
00:19:25,599 --> 00:19:27,870
Thank you, Brother Yinan.

179
00:19:27,870 --> 00:19:29,430
There, there.

180
00:19:36,510 --> 00:19:39,090
If you want it, see if you can get it.

181
00:19:58,060 --> 00:20:01,349
Qingchun. Qingchun!

182
00:20:01,349 --> 00:20:02,930
Qingchun!

183
00:20:29,170 --> 00:20:31,769
Heavens! Brother Yinan! How did you get this?

184
00:20:31,769 --> 00:20:34,169
You're awesome!

185
00:20:34,169 --> 00:20:35,809
You really got it for me!

186
00:20:35,810 --> 00:20:37,430
This...

187
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:42,229
Do you want to play basketball?

188
00:20:42,229 --> 00:20:44,729
Sure! Let me put this away first.

189
00:20:44,729 --> 00:20:46,700
This is awesome!

190
00:21:05,710 --> 00:21:07,370
What's wrong?

191
00:21:08,370 --> 00:21:10,570
I missed Kobe.

192
00:21:12,810 --> 00:21:16,260
He had formally said goodbye to this world.

193
00:21:16,260 --> 00:21:19,799
Of course, not. Didn't you read what the netizens posted?

194
00:21:19,799 --> 00:21:23,169
God wants to learn basketball, so he took Kobe away.

195
00:21:23,169 --> 00:21:26,369
The legend of him still stands in another space and time.

196
00:21:28,230 --> 00:21:30,620
Humans are too insignificant.

197
00:21:31,410 --> 00:21:34,690
We'll never know if tomorrow or mishaps will come first.

198
00:21:35,330 --> 00:21:36,800
Are you hungry?

199
00:21:38,990 --> 00:21:41,329
I want to eat the noodles you cook.

200
00:21:41,330 --> 00:21:43,989
Okay. I'll make it for you now.

201
00:21:49,960 --> 00:21:51,169
Here.

202
00:21:51,170 --> 00:21:54,670
Try and see if it tastes the same.

203
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:09,700
It's delicious. It tastes the same.

204
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:14,600
Since you cooked noodles for me,

205
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:17,700
I'll give you a surprise, then.

206
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:24,200
What's this?

207
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:25,900
Open it.

208
00:22:37,700 --> 00:22:40,800
This is the second half of Su Zhinian's life

209
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:43,600
with Song Qingchun from now on.

210
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:46,000
Throw the dice first.

211
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:50,400
Answer the question on the age where you've landed.

212
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:58,800
Age 32.

213
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:02,200
"What are you willing to do in exchange for?"

214
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:06,700
When I open my eyes every day,

215
00:23:06,700 --> 00:23:10,200
I wish I could see you in front of me.

216
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:12,300
Sweet talker.

217
00:23:12,300 --> 00:23:14,200
But don't you think there's something wrong with your sentence?

218
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:16,600
Shouldn't it be "I can see you every time

219
00:23:16,600 --> 00:23:18,100
I open my eyes every morning?"

220
00:23:18,100 --> 00:23:19,600
Isn't that so?

221
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:23,600
It's my turn.

222
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:30,300
Age 40.

223
00:23:30,300 --> 00:23:33,000
"Do you fear the passage of time?"

224
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,000
Yes.

225
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:36,000
I'm scared I'll grow old and ugly.

226
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,700
But I'm more afraid

227
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:41,300
if you aren't by my side at that time.

228
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:45,200
So always remember that my marital status

229
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:48,000
can only be "widowed," not "divorced".

230
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:51,800
If you loathe me for being old and cheat on me with young women,

231
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:53,600
be ready to face the consequences.

232
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:57,700
No matter how old you are,

233
00:23:57,700 --> 00:24:01,000
you will always look the same to me.

234
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:05,300
Your turn.

235
00:24:12,700 --> 00:24:14,400
It's my turn now.

236
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:20,300
Age 79.

237
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:25,000
"If you or your partner had to leave this world first, who do you wish that would be?"

238
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:28,800
I may be more selfish.

239
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:31,800
I hope I'll go first.

240
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:35,800
If possible, I'd wish the same.

241
00:24:35,800 --> 00:24:39,100
So I don't have to worry if you'll be sad when I'm no longer here.

242
00:24:39,100 --> 00:24:42,600
Or if anyone will bully you.

243
00:24:42,600 --> 00:24:46,200
If it'll hold you up for the rest of your life.

244
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:49,700
Why are you talking about such a serious topic all of a sudden?

245
00:24:49,700 --> 00:24:52,800
It's your turn now. It's the last question. Come on.

246
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:03,400
"If it's the end of the day tomorrow,

247
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:05,600
what do you want to do most now?"

248
00:25:15,500 --> 00:25:17,100
Let's get married.

249
00:25:18,100 --> 00:25:20,000
Get... Get married?

250
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:21,500
Now?

251
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:26,000
How?

252
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:42,800
I want to make the most of my limited life

253
00:25:42,800 --> 00:25:45,000
to be your partner.

254
00:25:47,100 --> 00:25:50,200
You're... You're Neo?

255
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:55,000
Are you done?

256
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:56,900
I'm almost done.

257
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:11,200
I'm not...

258
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:13,200
You can play games,

259
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:15,600
but complete this set of test papers first.

260
00:26:30,050 --> 00:26:34,070
[Create Character]

261
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:42,400
Heaven will be your witness.

262
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:44,200
The moon will be your matchmaker.

263
00:26:44,200 --> 00:26:47,800
Here you are, to be bonded in matrimony today.

264
00:26:47,800 --> 00:26:52,600
From today on, you'll help each other in hardships and love each other forever.

265
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:55,200
Even if it's a journey filled with hardships

266
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:57,600
and bitterness of the world,

267
00:26:57,600 --> 00:27:01,200
you'll live and die until the end of time.

268
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:04,300
So are you willing to do it?

269
00:27:10,600 --> 00:27:12,000
Yes.

270
00:27:13,600 --> 00:27:15,500
Me too.

271
00:27:15,500 --> 00:27:17,200
Wait a minute.

272
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:18,600
Our agreement is going to be due soon.

273
00:27:18,600 --> 00:27:21,400
Shouldn't we renew a new agreement?

274
00:27:27,400 --> 00:27:29,200
It's simple, just two clauses.

275
00:27:29,200 --> 00:27:32,200
First, I'm Party A, and you're Party B.

276
00:27:32,200 --> 00:27:35,100
Party A has the right to ask Party B to do anything.

277
00:27:35,100 --> 00:27:37,700
Second, the term of the agreement is fifty years.

278
00:27:37,700 --> 00:27:40,700
You shall not terminate it halfway.

279
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:43,000
All right.

280
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:44,500
Fifty years is a long time.

281
00:27:44,500 --> 00:27:47,400
After the agreement matures, as Party A, I shall request to extend the agreement.

282
00:27:47,400 --> 00:27:49,200
Don't worry.

283
00:27:55,800 --> 00:27:58,000
[Marriage Contract. Groom: Su Zhinian]
[Bride: Song Qingchun]

284
00:28:09,600 --> 00:28:11,500
The moon looks beautiful tonight.

285
00:28:50,900 --> 00:28:54,700
Tomorrow morning, I want preserved egg and lean meat porridge.

286
00:28:54,700 --> 00:28:56,300
Okay.

287
00:31:32,600 --> 00:31:36,600
If I don't go for the surgery, will anything happen within these three months?

288
00:31:36,600 --> 00:31:38,600
I'm not sure.

289
00:31:38,600 --> 00:31:42,100
Nothing might happen. But it may happen anytime...

290
00:31:43,100 --> 00:31:47,700
The side effects of the superpower are beyond our control now.

291
00:31:49,800 --> 00:31:51,000
Okay.

292
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:53,200
What's your plan?

293
00:31:53,200 --> 00:31:54,800
What about her?

294
00:31:57,300 --> 00:31:59,400
I'll still confess to her.

295
00:31:59,400 --> 00:32:03,400
Maybe it's selfish to do this.

296
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:05,800
But I want to tell her everything.

297
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:09,200
After that...

298
00:32:09,200 --> 00:32:13,200
No matter what you decide, I'll support you.

299
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:18,400
After that, I'll erase all her memories related to me.

300
00:32:18,400 --> 00:32:23,600
I'll transfer everyone related during this period away from her.

301
00:32:25,200 --> 00:32:27,100
So she'll only remember

302
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:31,600
that we're business partners, that's all.

303
00:32:39,200 --> 00:32:44,200
Based on your request, I've removed all of your news with Song Qingchun on the internet.

304
00:33:10,600 --> 00:33:12,700
[Arrogant Man]

305
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:16,800
[Delete contact]

306
00:33:21,070 --> 00:33:23,770
[Confirm]

307
00:33:31,300 --> 00:33:35,300
[Are you sure you want to delete this contact?]
]Delete]

308
00:33:55,400 --> 00:33:57,100
Sorry.

309
00:33:59,500 --> 00:34:01,400
Forget me.

310
00:36:34,400 --> 00:36:36,200
[100 Days SOHO Agreement]

311
00:37:54,600 --> 00:37:57,900
Since you're okay, I'll go home, then.

312
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:01,400
You haven't eaten, right?

313
00:38:02,400 --> 00:38:04,000
Sorry.

314
00:38:04,000 --> 00:38:06,000
Why don't you stay for a while?

315
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:22,000
I've ordered your favorite roasted pork brain.

316
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:23,400
Eat up.

317
00:38:24,600 --> 00:38:26,600
Where did you go in the afternoon?

318
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:30,800
Something came up.

319
00:38:32,500 --> 00:38:34,000
It's okay.

320
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:38,400
Emergencies like these happen in your profession all the time.

321
00:38:38,400 --> 00:38:42,100
Since there's nothing else, I'll get going, then.

322
00:38:57,200 --> 00:38:59,800
If you know being together

323
00:39:02,100 --> 00:39:04,700
will only hurt each other more,

324
00:39:05,600 --> 00:39:07,800
will you choose to start it?

325
00:39:07,800 --> 00:39:09,300
I will.

326
00:39:10,400 --> 00:39:12,500
As long as he's willing.

327
00:39:19,500 --> 00:39:21,000
Did you just do your medical checkup?

328
00:39:21,000 --> 00:39:22,800
A week ago.

329
00:39:22,800 --> 00:39:24,200
Be honest with me.

330
00:39:24,200 --> 00:39:26,400
Is it bad?

331
00:39:27,200 --> 00:39:31,200
Or... Or did you find out

332
00:39:31,200 --> 00:39:34,800
that we're actually half-siblings?

333
00:39:34,800 --> 00:39:36,600
That's why you avoided me this afternoon.

334
00:39:36,600 --> 00:39:40,900
You wanted to hire someone to play a heartless man, so I'll hate you and forget you.

335
00:39:40,900 --> 00:39:44,200
If it's the second reason, we have no choice, then.

336
00:39:44,200 --> 00:39:48,800
But if it's the first reason, no matter how bad it is, I still want to face it with you.

337
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:53,000
What do you think all day long?

338
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:55,600
Don't deny it. That's how it goes in novels.

339
00:39:55,600 --> 00:39:57,600
I'm really okay.

340
00:39:57,600 --> 00:39:59,700
Stop writing novels already.

341
00:40:04,600 --> 00:40:09,600
If I have a disease, will you face everything with me?

342
00:40:12,300 --> 00:40:14,800
Then are you willing to be my girlfriend?

343
00:40:18,000 --> 00:40:19,500
Yes.

